OL,3,CHistoric Tudor house to be mothballed
OL,4,Cdue to council cuts
OL,6,FCouncil leader Sean Morgan said: "We
OL,7,Fappreciate many will be disappointed
OL,8,Fby this decision, but the current
OL,9,Fsubsidy of #485,000 to run the site is
OL,10,Funsustainable in the current financial
OL,11,Fclimate.
OL,13,F"A similar decision was made earlier
OL,14,Fthis year to close Coffi Vista in
OL,15,FCaerphilly and we are now looking
OL,16,Fforward to the building reopening with
OL,17,Fan exciting new future, without
OL,18,Frequiring a council subsidy.
OL,20,F"This is what we hope to replicate at
OL,21,FLlancaiach Fawr."
